        "cooked": "<p>All works fine locally in OpenSCAD, and i am doing a subtractive operation. i am referencing the file by filename only, as locally it is in the same directory and when uploaded to my model on makerworld it is just in the root alonside the scad file itself. If i upload a scad file with only the import line in it, it fails validation. It just seems that the validation is happening somewhere that the stl file does not exist</p>",
