      {
        "accepted_answer": false,
        "actions_summary": [],
        "admin": false,
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.bambulab.com/malctheoracle/{size}/137308_2.png",
        "badges_granted": [],
        "bookmarked": false,
        "can_accept_answer": false,
        "can_delete": false,
        "can_edit": false,
        "can_recover": false,
        "can_see_hidden_post": false,
        "can_unaccept_answer": false,
        "can_view_edit_history": true,
        "can_wiki": false,
        "cooked": "<p>If I understand your question correctly:;</p>\n<p>You have an OpenSCAD file which you wish to use in the Parametric Model Maker (PMM), that script uses the OpenSCAD method <em>Import</em>, which is used to reference an external file and include it with your model.</p>\n<p>Nope.</p>\n<p>Despite my repeated requests to allow the designer to upload additional files for use of the <em>Import</em> method, they read that (likely while drinking alcohol p) and got confused.  They added a feature that let the user upload a file from the users local machine and not by the designer.</p>\n<p>You can learn about it here.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"91853\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://forum.bambulab.com/user_avatar/forum.bambulab.com/ypy/48/43830_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://forum.bambulab.com/t/paramatric-model-maker-v0-8-0-support-uploading-files/91853\">Paramatric Model Maker V0.8.0 support uploading files!</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/makerworld/144\"><span data-category-id=\"144\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #3AB54A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Section dedicated to MakerWorld, a 3D model platform that seamlessly links printers, model creators, and users.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">MakerWorld</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    <a name=\"english-version-1\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#english-version-1\"></a>English Version\nThe new version 0.8.0, scheduled for release on August 6, will include file upload support! Currently, only PNG, SVG, and STL formats are supported. \n <a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://cdn-forum.bambulab.com/original/3X/1/1/11bf70207c178877c76f0dd39fb1db0cfdf4960e.png\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/2x0gNLGShoThSuBxU7LfzWoSjNk.png?dl=1\" title=\"image\">[image]</a> \nTo meet the customization needs of general users, certain limitations have been implemented in the current version: \n\nSource code developers must create a variable name for a file before others can upload files:\n\n\nFor example, you must first define fileName = \"default.png\"; before others can use fileName to upload a file.\n\n\u2026\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
